  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Oxfam Cash for Protection Project (CfP)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The aim is to provide cash assistance to up to 275 households, representing approximately 1,650 individuals in the governorates of Ninewa and Salahadin with an average payment of GBP115 per individual. In line with internal cash for protection guidelines (Annex 1), a payment will be made to individuals or families based on the threats, vulnerabilities, exposure, and capacities identified and assessed.  Oxfam follows a risk reduction model that reduces risk to the individual or their family by addressing the threats, vulnerabilities, amount of exposure, and the current capacity they have to respond. Payments will be disbursed in the allocated timeframe, dependent on urgency of the case. A referral process is established through Oxfam fieldworker referrals, external service referrals, and peer referrals by existing community based structures. Based on the referral process, team will conduct assessment to analyse the type of needed support for identified beneficiaries.</narrative>
  </description>
